title: DAY-Shift Report 1/16/2021 Sun
text: PROGRAM: SPEAR to BEAMS delivering 500mA to users with top-off every 5 mins. BEAMLINES: All open except BL17. FAULTS: None. EXPERIMENTS: 1000 BL4-1 new users online. EOD required when hazardous gas and high temperatures in use (today through Tuesday). OPERATIONS: 1715 LN tank 5B at 72 inches. Tom from Airgas estimated a delivery at 10am tomorrow.

title: Day Shift HRS-Log
text: 01/16/22 14:00 - Randy Hollis - C0 (common) - HRS.SL.00-Installed spinning rotor gauges and connected Agilent turbo carts to both transfer lines. 01/16/22 12:30 - Roland Evans - C0 (common) - HRS.00.00-I did the plant walk through i found no issues. 01/16/22 08:30 - Roland Evans - C0 (common) - HRS.SL.VG-Supported Randy with his surface transfer line vacuum installations

title: shop
text: Worked on EMHP inspection and testing Spare Power Supply for LI29 ready for Xport to Gallery

title: Swing shift HRS-log
text: 01/16/22 14:30 - Mike Stivala - C0 (common) - HRS..-Completed plant walk down. No changes.

title: Shift summary: Sunday swing
text: SUMMARY: User beam for all of this 12-hour shift. The average fill rate was about 42mA/minute, and average calculated efficiency was about 90%. INJECTOR: 300mV Q. Tuned once between fills and did BTS trajectory correction. SPEAR: 500mA autofill topoffs every 5 minutes, as scheduled. BEAMLINES: The duty operator reports that the site liquid nitrogen tank is critically low, and beamlines with LN-cooled monos will close at midnight unless the Airgas truck shows up.

text: Low level of LN reported in recent BLDO shift reports. LN delivery expected in about 10 hours.

title: NIGHT-SHIFT Report 2022-01-16/17, Sun/Mon; Martin Luther King Jr Day
text: NIGHT-SHIFT Report 2022-01-16/17, Sun/Mon; Martin Luther King Jr Day PROGRAM: User Beam, 500 mA, 300 s top-off injection BEAMLINES: 1730 All open except BL17 0000 All closed except BL1, BL2, BL4, BL5, BL8, BL13, BL14 & BL16 0100 BL4 closed FAULTS: None EXPERIMENTS: 1715 Assisted experimenter on BL2-3 to open hutch 1725 Assisted experimenter on BL9-3 to obtain LN at fill station 1930 LN critically low, below 70 ins, with no delivery apparently until 1000 tomorrow. Plan formed to close the LN-mono served beamlines at 0000 (BL4 to be delayed until 0100) 2100 Assisted experimenter on BL7-3 to find a mirror, loaned from DO station 0000 Repeated failures of Airgas to deliver LN have forced experimentation stoppage and BL closure on BL4, BL6, BL7, BL9, BL10, BL11, BL12 & BL15 0015 Dialed back pump frequencies on Messer-controlled LN Mono pumps, for LN preservation; data listed below to aid restorative protocol 0500 Relaxation of LN depletion gradient noted per BL closure: 0.8 ins/hr over last 5 hrs c.f. 1.67 ins/hr over previous 48 hrs DATA: LN Mono (Messer) BL SC fill IL fill Pump-0 Pump-1 (35-100)% (21-35)% Hz Hz 7-3 60 35 64 40 7-2 100 30 46.2 30 10-2 50 35 40 30 9-3 85 35 64.4 40 9-2 90 35 51.2 30 12-2 70 35 60 40 6-2 40 33 76.8 50 11-2 75 35 54 30 4-3 85 35 65 40 4-2 100 32 58 30 4-1 90 35 65 40 LN Mono (Siemens/RI) BL SC fill IL fill Pump-0 Pump-1 (35-75)% (15-28)% Hz Hz 12-1 52 28 30 unchanged 15-2 70 27 30 unchanged 17-2 70 30 30 unchanged

text: SUMMARY: User beam delivery. INJECTOR: Autofill RUN mode. 43mA/min injection rates at greater than 100 percent calculated efficiency. SPEAR: User beam delivered with no beam losses or missed fills. BEAM LINES: Eight beam lines were closed at the start of the shift due to inadequate LN2 supply. The delivery truck which had been delayed was onsite and filling the SSRL dewar at 10:00AM. The BL Duty Op then began opening the affected beam lines. All beam lines open except for BL-17 by 10:30AM.
